<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"We're all trying to get out of it, to be hone=
st," said Andrea Walne, a general partner at Manhattan Venture Partners.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">MVP committed to invest in the deal earlier th=
is year, but a question remains as to whether the firm and others will actu=
ally be on the hook for the full amount they committed to, according to Wal=
ne. "We talked to the other investors, everyone's trying to get out of it, =
no one thinks the company should be valued at $44 billion," she said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Citing the sharp downturn in equity markets ov=
er the last 6 months, Walne said she would put the value of Twitter at this=
 point closer to $10 billion to $12 billion, a far cry from the $44 billion=
 that Musk has agreed to pay.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Look selfishly I am hoping that some of them b=
ack out and he sues them, arguing that in fact the deal was never terminate=
d and Twitter is still worth $44 billion. That would be a great continuatio=
n to this story. But, no, my assumption is that most of them won=E2=80=99t =
back out (to avoid offending Musk), but if they do he won=E2=80=99t sue the=
m (because it=E2=80=99s not worth it). But I confess that I don=E2=80=99t u=
nderstand=C2=A0<em>this=C2=A0</em>strategy. If you go around=C2=A0<em>telli=
ng journalists on the record=C2=A0</em>that you=E2=80=99re trying to get ou=
t of it, then you are offending Musk! But you might still send in the money=
, for a deal you hate! The move is to say nothing and=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</e=
m>send in the money.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere, the Information reports that =E2=80=
=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29401395.284514=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlaW5mb3JtYXRpb24uY29tL2FydGljbGVzL211c2std2lsbC1oYXZlLW=
Fic29sdXRlLWNvbnRyb2wtb3Zlci10d2l0dGVyLWRvY3VtZW50cy1zaG93P3V0bV9zb3VyY2U9c=
2cmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249YXJ0aWNsZV9lbWFpbCZ1dG1fY29udGVu=
dD1hcnRpY2xlLTg5MTImcmM9MWJkaTVo/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB42c0417c" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
>Musk Will Have Absolute Control Over Twitter, Documents Show</a>=E2=80=9D:=
</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk may be relying on outside investors =
to help finance his $44 billion purchase of Twitter. But that doesn=E2=80=
=99t mean he=E2=80=99s giving those investors a say in how the company is r=
un.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A shareholders=E2=80=99 agreement prepared by =
Musk=E2=80=99s lawyers for equity investors shows that Musk will retain abs=
olute authority over key decisions. He will have =E2=80=9Csole discretion=
=E2=80=9D to decide whether to pursue a sale of the company, an initial pub=
lic offering or some other refinancing transaction involving the business, =
for instance.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yeah I can=E2=80=99t imagine doing it any othe=
r way. He=E2=80=99s putting in the majority of the equity check, it was his=
 idea, and he=E2=80=99s Elon Musk. Nobody signed up for this deal planning =
to=C2=A0<em>supervise=C2=A0</em>how Musk runs Twitter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/29401395.284514/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2xvd2JvcmluZy5jb20vcC9lbG9u=
LW11c2tzLWJ1c2luZXNzLXRpZXMtZGVzZXJ2ZQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB03f530e7" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">Matt Yglesias notes</a> that Musk=E2=80=99s ties to China (in his ro=
le as the head of Tesla Inc.) might make it hard for him to run Twitter on =
=E2=80=9Cfree speech=E2=80=9D lines:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Does this mean that a Musk-run Twi=
tter is going to impose China-friendly censorship as heavy-handed as the se=
lf-censorship Musk practices in his personal commentary? That he=E2=80=99s =
going to turn it into a China-free zone the way that Apple has with its con=
tent business?</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CProbably not,=E2=80=9D he answers, bu=
t the worry seems fair:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What does Twitter do once it=E2=80=
=99s owned by the CEO of a major industrial brand? I don=E2=80=99t know, bu=
t I wish the reporters on the Musk beat would ask. And frankly, I wish Cong=
ress and the FTC would, too.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The problem is, what do you do about it?<a cla=
ss=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent=
 !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>=C2=A0You could imagine a world in which the US government had some sor=
t of regulatory apparatus for social media companies that:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Had some rules about how they treat c=
ontent;=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Had a regulatory age=
ncy that wrote and enforced those rules;</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom:=
 5px;">Had pre-merger review that could approve or reject acquisitions base=
d on the suitability of a new owner, or could extract conditions (=E2=80=9C=
You can run Twitter, but you can=E2=80=99t censor content on behalf of Chin=
a=E2=80=9D) for approving an acquisition.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are regimes sort of like that for other =
industries =E2=80=94=C2=A0if you want to buy a casino, gaming regulators wi=
ll take a hard look at your personal qualifications =E2=80=94=C2=A0but soci=
al media rose to prominence in a deregulatory age, plus, can you imagine ho=
w this system would actually=C2=A0<em>work? (</em>Would the Federal Social =
Media Agency require Twitter to ban anti-Semitic tweets, or require it to a=
llow them?) And so in practice Musk=E2=80=99s acquisition of Twitter got re=
viewed mainly for antitrust concerns, and there were none, so it was quickl=
y approved. I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2940=
1395.284514/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjI=
tMDQtMTUvc3VyZS1lbG9uLW11c2stbWlnaHQtYnV5LXR3aXR0ZXI_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAxNzIyX0=
1PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlc=
m09MjIxMDE3JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcf24df=
47" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> wrote back in April</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is not in a heavily regulated i=
ndustry, and there=E2=80=99s no particular antitrust problem with Musk acqu=
iring it. =E2=80=9CWorld=E2=80=99s richest person acquires the main venue f=
or public communication=E2=80=9D does seem like the sort of thing that ough=
t to raise regulatory concerns, but in our actually existing system I=E2=80=
=99m not sure what those concerns would be.=C2=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I mean, I can see the=C2=A0<em>concerns=C2=A0<=
/em>that it raises, but not the=C2=A0<em>regulatory=C2=A0</em>concerns.</p>
